            <h4>LL04 Frequenty Asked Questions</h4>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL04-037/">LL04-037 "Chika Takami"</a> to <a href="/card/LL04-045/">LL04-045 "Ruby
                    Kurosawa"</a></h5>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#member_counting">How do I count Members?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="037">
                When counting "differently named <span class="redtext">"Aqours"</span> Members", should I count the card that has this Skill, too?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Yes. They count as well.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL04-046/">LL04-046 "Chika Takami"</a></h5>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#stand_by">What is the "On Stand-By" state?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#member_counting">How do I count Members?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#more_less">If a Skill's condition says "more/less than", does it also
                    count if you have the same amount?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="046">
                At the time I <%- skillFormat("⟪ENTER⟫") %>ed this Member, there were eight other Members on Stand-By. Can I <%- skillFormat("⟪SCOUT⟫") %>using
                this Skill?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                No. This Member counts as well, so there are nine Members on Stand-By and the Skill's condition is not
                met.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL04-047/">LL04-047 "Riko Sakurauchi"</a></h5>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#skill_order_multiple_skills">What if a Member card has two or more
                    Skills?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#join_success_order">What is the order for <%- skillFormat("[Live Join]/[Live Success]") %>
                    Skills?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="047">
                If two or more of this card join a <%- skillFormat("⟪LIVE⟫") %>, can I flip further Song cards?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Yes. For example, if two of this <span class="redtext">"Riko"</span> card join a <%- skillFormat("⟪LIVE⟫, you can, together with the one Song card you flip from performing a ⟪LIVE⟫") %> by default, flip a total of three cards.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL04-048/">LL04-048 "Kanan Matsuura"</a></h5>
            <div class="question" id="048">
                The card I returned from my Hand to the bottom of my Deck to use the <%- skillFormat("[Entry] Skill was the last card in my Hand. Can I still choose the ⟪ENTER⟫") %> option?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Yes. As long as you return a card to the bottom of your Deck, you can choose either.<br>
                If you don't have any cards in your Hand, you can't <%- skillFormat("⟪ENTER⟫") %> a card from your Hand, which means you can't do anything when picking that option.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL04-049/">LL04-049 "Dia Kurosawa"</a></h5>
            <div class="question" id="049">
                What happens if the top card of the Deck is flipped face-up, or the Deck is empty?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Even if the card is visible to them, the next player must "guess" whether it has <%- skillFormat("Stars") %> or not, then use the effect corresponding to the answer.<br>
                If your Deck is empty, you cannot use this Skill.
            </div>

