            <h5><a href="/card/LL04-052/">LL04-052 "Hanamaru Kunikida"</a></h5>
            <div class="question" id="052">
                Can the other players choose to not draw a card?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                No. You always draw three cards, and the other players always draw one card each.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL04-060/">LL04-060 "Todokanai Hoshi da to Shitemo"</a></h5>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#join_success_order">What is the order for <%- skillFormat("[Live Join]/[Live Success]") %>
                    Skills?</a>
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL04-061/">LL04-061 "Yozora wa Nandemo Shitteru no?"</a></h5>
            <div class="question" id="061_member">
                Is the draw limit increased by one even if I <%- skillFormat("⟪SCOUT⟫") %> using a Skill like the one of <a href="/card/LL04-046/">LL04-046 "Chika Takami"</a>?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Yes. Even if you use a Skill to do so, <%- skillFormat("⟪SCOUT⟫") %>ing will always get +1 extra card. Note that Skills such as "Draw X cards" are not <%- skillFormat("⟪SCOUT⟫") %>s, so you cannot draw extra cards.
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="061_out">
                The player who used this Song card for a Live has won. Is the <%- skillFormat("[While Live]") %> Skill still active after
                that?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Yes. <%- skillFormat("[While Live]") %> Skills will be active until the end of the game.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL04-062/">LL04-062 "Tokimeki Bunruigaku"</a></h5>
            <div class="question" id="062">
                <a href="/card/LL04-053/">LL04-053 "Mari Ohara"</a> is joining this <%- skillFormat("⟪LIVE⟫, after I chose to use [RUSH] when I ⟪ENTER⟫ed her. Will she still gain +[ALL] from this Song card's Skill?") %>
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Yes. She has a <%- skillFormat("[LIVE] icon, so she will gain +[ALL]") %>.
            </div>

